hdr-phdi.def:
PHDI discounts the HDI for pressures on the planet to reflect a concern for intergenerational inequality, similar to the Inequality-adjusted HDI adjustment which is motivated by a concern for intragenerational inequality. It is computed as the product of the HDI and (1 – index of planetary pressures) where (1 – index of planetary pressures) can be seen as an adjustment factor.

PHDI is the level of human development adjusted by carbon dioxide emissions per person (production-based) and material footprint per capita to account for the excessive human pressure on the planet.
hdr-phdi.name: Planetary pressures–adjusted Human Development Index (value)
hdr-phdi.source: Calculated as the product of the HDI and the adjustment factor presented in column 5.
